00:00:52.359 --> 00:00:57.019
cut. So, the point is we're trying to get
as much of an R-Value as we possibly can with

00:00:57.019 --> 00:01:02.399
all the insulation, and the envelope that
surrounds this entire house. We've also done

00:01:02.399 --> 00:01:08.820
this with our windows and our doors. We've
made sure they're all Energy Star rated so

00:01:08.820 --> 00:01:13.971
we can get that maximum energy efficiency
from these. Because here's the deal, if you

00:01:13.971 --> 00:01:19.360
take and you look at your expenses, the cost
of utilities in a year, if you break it down,

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:23.610
